   Mapping, in which there was one-to-one mapping between two sounds and
   two locations; and Mixed Mapping, in which the two sounds were equally
   likely to appear at either one of the two locations. We surmised that
   only neurons tuned to both location and frequency should be
   differentially adapted by the Mixed and Fixed mappings. Replicating our
   previous findings, we found adaptation to spatial location in the PT
   Importantly, activation was higher for Mixed Mapping than for Fixed
   Mapping blocks, even though the two sounds and the two locations
   appeared equally in both conditions. These results show that spatially
   tuned neurons in the human PT are not invariant to the spectral content
   of sounds.}},
